output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who are current living in each region 5 years after graduation, male and female Level 7 (research) graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext: For Level 7 (research) graduates of Medicine and dentistry'' in the ''Education'' industry ''5'' years after graduation, the region that saw the highest number of students studying there was ''North West''. The region with the lowest number of students studying there was ''North East''. The region with the highest number of graduates living there ''5'' years after graduation was ''West Midlands'' and the region with the least graduates living there was ''East Midlands''.
output.maptext2:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the highest proportionate increase in graduates who studied there compared to living
                    there 5 years after graduation is Yorkshire and the Humber, where the number of
                    graduates increased by 0%. The region with the largest
                    decrease is London where the number of graduates decreased by -99.2%.
